## SIMULATION ARCHITECTURE\
\
Implement these functions (all in one file):\
\
### 
\f1\fs26 \cb4 get_thrust(t)
\f0\fs28 \cb3  \
numpy.interp on THRUST_DATA. Returns 0 for t > BURN_TIME.\
\
### 
\f1\fs26 \cb4 kalman_update(state, P, gyro_rate_dps, accel_angle_deg, dt)
\f0\fs28 \cb3 \
Standard 2-state linear Kalman filter.\
State = [angle_deg, gyro_bias_dps]\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qr\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf5 \cb6 \strokec5 \
\
\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf8 \strokec8 F = [[1, -dt], [0, 1]]\
B = [dt, 0]\
H = [1, 0]\
Q = [[Q_ANGLE, 0], [0, Q_RATE]]\
R = R_MEASURE\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Returns (new_state, new_P)\
\
### 
\f1\fs26 \cb4 pid_update(error, prev_error, integral, dt, prev_output)
\f0\fs28 \cb3 \
Returns (output_clamped, new_integral, raw_output)\
- proportional = KP * error\
- integral += KI * error * dt, clamped to \'b1GIMBAL_LIMIT (anti-windup)\
- derivative = KD * (error - prev_error) / dt\
- raw = P + I + D\
- rate-limited: constrain raw vs prev_output \'b1 SERVO_RATE_LIM*dt\
- hard clamp to \'b1GIMBAL_LIMIT\
- Returns achieved gimbal angle\
\
### 
\f1\fs26 \cb4 run_simulation(theta0_deg, rate0_deg_s=0.0, open_loop=False, disturbance=None, wind_mag=0.0, thrust_scale=1.0, gimbal_limit_override=None, seed=None)
\f0\fs28 \cb3 \
\
RK4 rotational dynamics at DT_SIM.\
Control loop fires every round(1/(CONTROL_HZ * DT_SIM)) physics steps.\
\
Physics per step (with aerodynamic damping \'97 CRITICAL, do not omit):\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qr\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf5 \cb6 \strokec5 \
\
\
\
\
\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf8 \strokec8 F_T = get_thrust(t) * thrust_scale\
tau_tvc = F_T * MOMENT_ARM * sin(radians(gimbal_angle))\
v = sqrt(2 * F_T / ROCKET_MASS)   # approximate velocity\
q_dyn = 0.5 * AIR_DENSITY * v**2\
A_cs = pi * ROCKET_RADIUS**2\
tau_aero_damp = -AERO_DAMP_COEFF * radians(angular_rate) * q_dyn * A_cs * CP_OFFSET\
tau_wind = wind_lat * CP_OFFSET    # wind_lat injected if disturbance active\
alpha = degrees((tau_tvc + tau_aero_damp + tau_wind) / MOI)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Sensor noise (added to true state to produce IMU readings):\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qr\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf5 \cb6 \strokec5 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf8 \strokec8 gyro_reading = true_rate + N(0, GYRO_NOISE_STD)\
accel_angle  = true_angle + N(0, ACCEL_NOISE_STD)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Post-burnout: add GYRO_DRIFT_RATE * dt to gyro_reading cumulatively to simulate drift.\
\
Log every physics step: time, true_angle, true_rate, kalman_angle, kalman_rate,\
gimbal_cmd, gimbal_actual, accel_reading (raw), gyro_reading (raw), thrust.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf2 \cb4 disturbance
\f0\fs28 \cb3  parameter: dict with keys 
\f1\fs26 \cb4 torque_Nm
\f0\fs28 \cb3 , 
\f1\fs26 \cb4 start_s
\f0\fs28 \cb3 , 
\f1\fs26 \cb4 duration_s
\f0\fs28 \cb3 \
Apply disturbance torque as tau_wind during the disturbance window.\
\
Return dict with all logged arrays as numpy arrays.\
