## CRITICAL PHYSICS NOTES (bugs that were in the original \'97 ensure these are FIXED)\
\
1. Aerodynamic damping MUST be included: tau_aero_damp = -AERO_DAMP_COEFF * radians(rate) * q_dyn * A_cs * CP_OFFSET. Without it, angular rate stays constant during coast (unphysical).\
\
2. Wind torque MUST use CP_OFFSET as moment arm, not an arbitrary number.\
\
3. Accelerometer noise MUST be in angle-equivalent degrees (not g-units \'d7 rad conversion). ACCEL_NOISE_STD = 2.5 degrees.\
\
4. The raw accelerometer line in fig08 MUST use the logged accel_reading array from the simulation run, NOT freshly synthesized noise. Log it during the simulation loop and reuse it.\
\
5. Open-loop simulation: gimbal stays at 0, no PID runs, rocket holds initial angle throughout burn (no aerodynamic restoring force).\
