\ls1\ilvl0
\f2 \cf2 \cb6 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Saturation is 1.0% cumulative, not "essentially 0".
\f0 \'a0With KP = 8.5 and \uc0\u952 \u8320  = 5\'b0, the initial command is 42.5\'b0, so the gimbal unavoidably pegs at -10\'b0 for one ~34 ms window during the tip-over correction, and never again. fig05 shows the true curve with an annotation explaining this; the spec's \'b10.05% ylim would have pushed the line off-axis.\cb1 \
